WEBVTT

00:13.722 --> 00:15.265
That man loved life.

00:15.349 --> 00:18.852
I'm not denying
that Emmett had medical issues,

00:19.353 --> 00:21.188
but he never let it get him down.

00:21.688 --> 00:24.483
He had a passion for life.

00:26.401 --> 00:27.402
Emmett…

00:29.029 --> 00:31.657
he made you appreciate
your good fortune.

00:31.740 --> 00:34.243
'Cause even though he was strapped
in a hospital bed,

00:35.035 --> 00:38.372
he was more alive
than most folks who can use their legs.

00:39.748 --> 00:43.919
He loved to laugh. He loved people.

00:45.170 --> 00:48.298
I'm sorry you lost him. I am.

00:49.174 --> 00:53.762
I didn't lose him. He was taken from me.

00:55.222 --> 00:59.643
Did Emmett say anything
about what was going on at LifeCare?

00:59.726 --> 01:02.229
Did-- Did you talk to him
on that last Thursday?

01:02.980 --> 01:05.232
His phone wasn't working by then.

01:05.315 --> 01:09.862
I tried reaching him
on Wednesday and Thursday.

01:12.906 --> 01:14.324
Before that, he said that--

01:14.408 --> 01:18.996
you know, th-- things were a little crazy,
but he didn't dwell on that.

01:20.330 --> 01:22.040
He didn't wanna worry me.

01:24.376 --> 01:28.213
He even was joking
about what he had for breakfast.

01:28.839 --> 01:33.760
Said he had canned tuna fish and crackers…

01:34.970 --> 01:36.305
and relish.

01:39.016 --> 01:40.767
Said it was delicious.

01:42.853 --> 01:46.607
My Emmett. He was a fighter.

01:48.150 --> 01:50.611
And for him to have died
of his own accord?

01:51.278 --> 01:52.613
That don't make no sense.

01:53.739 --> 01:56.325
None. Whatsoever.

